of Group-A and Group-B (Gazetted) Officers.
Age 50/55 years of age or qualifying
Service on completion of 30 years of service
About the review...
Government of Maharashtra
Department of Higher and Technical Education
Government Decision No. Narrow-2024 / No.90 (E-6800367) / MASHI-1
Madam Cama Road, Martyrdom Rajguru Chowk,
Mantralaya, Mumbai 400 032.
Date: July 10, 2024.
Read:
1) Government Decisions, General Administration Department, No.LPL-2017 / Q.No.21 / Q.15,
Government Order, Department of Higher and Technical Education, No. Narrow-2021 / No.310 / Mashi-1,
The Government's Decisions:
Pursuant to Rule 10 (4) and Rule 65 of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Pension) Rules, 1982
Administrative Officer on Establishment of Directorate of Higher Education, Group-A & Minor Administration
Officers, Group-B cadre officers at the age of 50/55 or on attaining the age of 30 years
Eligibility to Remain in Service - Principal Secretary (Department of Higher and Technical Education) to try ineligibility
The Review Committee chaired by him met on Monday, dated 08/07/2024
As per the recommendation of the Review Committee and with the approval of the competent authority:
Officers in service beyond the age of 50/55 years or on completion of 30 years of qualifying service
are being determined to be eligible to stay.
